{"kind":"article","topicSectionsStyle":"detailedGrid","sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/06-07-corporate-and-football-penalties","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"date: 2015-06-07T21:55:14-05:00"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"What if the penalties in football were more like the penalties in the corporate world? What if, instead of negating any forward progress, penalties were simply subtracted from the gains?"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This would create a remarkably different game. There’d be penalties on every down! A holding call on a 15 yard run would result in a 10 yard gain. Penalties would no longer be a deterrent to illegal play, they’d just be part of a good strategy."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/brunow\/06-07-corporate-and-football-penalties"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"metadata":{"platforms":[{"name":"Brunow","introducedAt":"2017.01.20"}],"title":"Corporate and Football Penalties","modules":[{"name":"Brunow"}],"color":{"standardColorIdentifier":"purple"}},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow","doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/Archive","doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/2015"]]},"references":{"doc://Brunow/documentation/Brunow":{"type":"topic","role":"collection","title":"Brunow","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"David Brunow, known as Brunow [ˈbɹunoʊ] to the folks he works with, is a human living on Earth. You might have something in common with him — if you think it is ridiculous that he is talking about himself in the first person here, so does he.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow","url":"\/documentation\/brunow"},"doc://Brunow/documentation/Brunow/Archive":{"type":"topic","kind":"article","role":"collectionGr